  "prompt": "The closer you are to the person, the more likely they will betray you? True or False? Like Lucifer the fallen angel?",
  "response": "The statement \"The closer you are to the person, the more likely they will betray you\" is not universally true or false. Human relationships are complex and vary greatly from one individual to another. Some people find that their closest relationships are the most trustworthy and fulfilling, while others may experience betrayal from those they believed to be closest to them.\n\nThe reference to Lucifer, the fallen angel, is a specific religious and mythological story which may suggest that betrayal can come from those who are closest or most trusted. However, it is important to understand that this is a symbolic narrative rather than a definitive rule applicable to all personal relationships.\n\nIn general, trust and betrayal are nuanced aspects of human interaction that cannot be universally defined by proximity or closeness. Each relationship is unique and influenced by a wide variety of factors.",
